<inglise> COUNCIL DIRECTIVE 92/49/EEC of 18 June 1992 on the coordination of laws, regulations and administrative provisions relating to direct insurance other than life assurance and amending Directives 73/239/EEC and 88/357/EEC (third non-life insurance Directive) </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU DIREKTIIV 92/49/EM&Uuml; otsekindlustusega, v&auml;lja arvatud elukindlustusega seotud &otilde;igusnormide koosk&otilde;lastamise kohta, millega muudetakse direktiive 73/239/EM&Uuml; ja 88/375/EM&Uuml; (kolmas kahjukindlustuse direktiiv) 18. juuni 1992 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> Euroopa &uuml;henduste n&otilde;ukogu, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community, and in particular Articles 57 (2) and 66 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artikli 57 l&otilde;iget 2 ja artiklit 66, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission(1), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Komisjoni ettepanekut, (1) </eesti>
<inglise> In cooperation with the European Parliament(2), </inglise>
<eesti> koost&ouml;&ouml;s Euroopa Parlamendiga, (2) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the Economic and Social Committee(3), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse majandus- ja sotsiaalkomitee arvamust (3) </eesti>
<inglise> (1) Whereas it is necessary to complete the internal market in direct insurance other than life assurance from the point of view both of the right of establishment and of the freedom to provide services, to make it easier for insurance undertakings with head offices in the Community to cover risks situated within the Community; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: 1) vaja on v&auml;lja kujundada otsekindlustuse, v&auml;lja arvatud elukindlustuse siseturg, pidades silmas nii asutamis&otilde;igust kui ka teenuste osutamise vabadust, et muuta &uuml;henduses asuvate riskide kindlustamine h&otilde;lpsamaks &uuml;henduses asuva peakontoriga kindlustusseltsidele; </eesti>
<inglise> (2) Whereas the Second Council Directive of 22 June 1988 on the coordination of laws, regulations and administrative provisions relating to direct insurance other than life assurance and laying down provisions to facilitate the effective exercise of freedom to provide services and amending Directive 72/239/EEC (88/357/EEC) (4) has already contributed substantially to the achievement of the internal market in direct insurance other than life assurance by granting policyholders who, by virtue of their status, their size or the nature of the risks to be insured, do not require special protection in the Member State in which a risk is situated complete freedom to avail themselves of the widest possible insurance market; </inglise>
<eesti> 2) 22. juuni 1998. aasta n&otilde;ukogu teine direktiiv otsekindlustusega, v&auml;lja arvatud elukindlustusega seotud &otilde;igusnormide koosk&otilde;lastamise kohta, millega n&auml;hakse ette s&auml;tted teenuste osutamise vabaduse tegeliku kasutamise h&otilde;lbustamiseks ja muudetakse direktiivi 73/239/EM&Uuml; (88/357/EM&Uuml;), on juba andnud olulise panuse otsekindlustuse, v&auml;lja arvatud elukindlustuse siseturu loomiseks, v&otilde;imaldades kindlustusv&otilde;tjatele, kes oma seisundi, suuruse v&otilde;i kindlustatavate riskide laadi t&otilde;ttu ei vaja erilist kaitset riski asukohaliikmesriigis, t&auml;ieliku vabaduse kasutada v&otilde;imalikult avarat kindlustusturgu; </eesti>
<inglise> (3) Whereas Directive 88/357/EEC therefore represents an important stage in the merging of national markets into an integrated market and that stage must be supplemented by other Community instruments with a view to enabling all policyholders, irrespective of their status, their size or the nature of the risks to be insured, to have recourse to any insurer with a head office in the Community who carries on business there, under the right of establishment or the freedom to provide services, while guaranteeing them adequate protection; </inglise>
<eesti> 3) seet&otilde;ttu on direktiiv 88/357/EM&Uuml; t&auml;htis etapp siseriiklike turgude &uuml;hendamisel integreeritud turuks ja seda etappi tuleb t&auml;iendada muude &uuml;henduse meetmetega, mille eesm&auml;rk on v&otilde;imaldada k&otilde;igil kindlustusv&otilde;tjatel s&otilde;ltumata nende seisundist, suurusest v&otilde;i kindlustatavate riskide laadist kasutada &uuml;ksk&otilde;ik millist kindlustusandjat, kelle peakontor asub &uuml;henduses ja kes seal asutamis&otilde;iguse v&otilde;i teenuste osutamise vabaduse alusel tegutseb, tagades neile samal ajal piisava kaitse; </eesti>
<inglise> (4) Whereas this Directive forms part of the body of Community legislation already enacted which includes the First Council Directive of 24 July 1973 on the coordination of laws, regulations and administrative provisions relating to the taking up and pursuit of the business of direct insurance other than life assurance (73/239/EEC) (5) and the Council Directive of 19 December 1991 on the annual accounts and consolidated accounts of insurance undertakings (91/674/EEC) (6); </inglise>
<eesti> 4) k&auml;esolev direktiiv on osa juba j&otilde;ustunud &uuml;henduse &otilde;igusaktide kogumist, mis h&otilde;lmab 24. juuli 1973. aasta esimese n&otilde;ukogu direktiivi otsekindlustustegevuse, v&auml;lja arvatud elukindlustustegevuse alustamise ja j&auml;tkamisega seotud &otilde;igusnormide koosk&otilde;lastamise kohta (73/239/EM&Uuml;) (5) ning n&otilde;ukogu 19. detsembri 1991. aasta direktiivi kindlustusseltside raamatupidamise aasta- ja &uuml;hendaruannete kohta (91/674/EM&Uuml;) (6); </eesti>
<inglise> (5) Whereas the approach adopted consists in bringing about such harmonization as is essential, necessary and sufficient to achieve the mutual recognition of authorizations and prudential control systems, thereby making it possible to grant a single authorization valid throughout the Community and apply the principle of supervision by the home Member State; </inglise>
<eesti> 5) vastuv&otilde;etud l&auml;henemisviis seisneb sellises &uuml;htlustamises, mis on elut&auml;htis, vajalik ja piisav tegevuslubade ja usaldatavusnormatiivide s&uuml;steemide vastastikuseks tunnustamiseks, v&otilde;imaldades seega anda &uuml;htse tegevusloa, mis kehtib kogu &uuml;henduses, ja kohaldada p&auml;ritoluliikmesriigi poolse j&auml;relevalve p&otilde;him&otilde;tet; </eesti>
<inglise> (6) Whereas, as a result, the taking up and the pursuit of the business of insurance are henceforth to be subject to the grant of a single official authorization issued by the competent authorities of the Member State in which an insurance undertaking has its head office; whereas such authorization enables an undertaking to carry on business throughout the Community, under the right of establishment or the freedom to provide services; whereas the Member State of the branch or of the provision of services may no longer require insurance undertakings which wish to carry on insurance business there and which have already been authorized in their home Member State to seek fresh authorization; whereas Directives 73/239/EEC and 88/357/EEC should therefore be amended along those lines; </inglise>
<eesti> 6) selle tulemusel s&otilde;ltub kindlustustegevuse alustamine ja j&auml;tkamine edaspidi &uuml;htse ametliku tegevusloa saamisest, mille annavad p&auml;devad asutused liikmesriigis, kus asub kindlustusseltsi peakontor; selline tegevusluba v&otilde;imaldab kindlustusseltsil tegutseda asutamis&otilde;iguse v&otilde;i teenuste osutamise vabaduse alusel kogu &uuml;henduses; liikmesriik, kus asub filiaal v&otilde;i kus osutatakse teenuseid, ei v&otilde;i enam n&otilde;uda, et kindlustusseltsid, kes soovivad seal j&auml;tkata kindlustustegevust ja kes on oma p&auml;ritoluliikmesriigis juba tegevusloa saanud, taotleksid uut luba; direktiive 73/239/EM&Uuml; ja 88/357/EM&Uuml; tuleks seet&otilde;ttu vastavalt muuta; </eesti>
<inglise> (7) Whereas the competent authorities of home Member States will henceforth be responsible for monitoring the financial health of insurance undertakings, including their state of solvency, the establishment of adequate technical provisions and the covering of those provisions by matching assets; </inglise>
<eesti> 7) p&auml;ritoluliikmesriikide p&auml;devad asutused vastutavad edaspidi kindlustusseltside finantsseisundi j&auml;lgimise eest, kaasa arvatud nende maksej&otilde;ulisus, piisavate kindlustustehniliste eraldiste loomine ja nende eraldiste tagamine vastavuses olevate varadega; </eesti>
<inglise> (8) Whereas certain provisions of this Directive define minimum standards; whereas a home Member State may lay down stricter rules for insurance undertakings authorized by its own competent authorities; </inglise>
<eesti> 8) teatavad k&auml;esoleva direktiivi s&auml;tted m&auml;&auml;ravad kindlaks minimaalsed standardid; p&auml;ritoluliikmesriik v&otilde;ib oma p&auml;devatelt asutustelt loa saanud kindlustusseltsidele s&auml;testada rangemad eeskirjad; </eesti>
<inglise> (9) Whereas the competent authorities of the Member States must have at their disposal such means of supervision as are necessary to ensure the orderly pursuit of business by insurance undertakings throughout the Community whether carried on under the right of establishment or the freedom to provide services; whereas, in particular, they must be able to introduce appropriate safeguards or impose sanctions aimed at preventing irregularities and infringements of the provisions on insurance supervision; </inglise>
<eesti> 9) liikmesriikide p&auml;devate asutuste k&auml;sutuses peavad olema j&auml;relevalvevahendid, mis on vajalikud kindlustusseltside korrap&auml;rase tegutsemise tagamiseks kogu &uuml;henduses kas asutamis&otilde;iguse v&otilde;i teenuste osutamise vabaduse alusel; eriti peab neil olema v&otilde;imalus kehtestada sobivaid julgeolekumeetmeid v&otilde;i rakendada sanktsioone, mille eesm&auml;rk on takistada eeskirjade eiramist ja kindlustuse j&auml;relevalve s&auml;tete rikkumist; </eesti>
<inglise> (10) Whereas the internal market comprises an area without internal frontiers and involves access to all insurance business other than life assurance throughout the Community and, hence, the possibility for any duly authorized insurer to cover any of the risks referred to in the Annex to Directive 73/239/EEC; whereas, to that end, the monopoly enjoyed by certain bodies in certain Member States in respect of the coverage of certain risks must be abolished; </inglise>
<eesti> 10) siseturg on sisepiirideta ala ja h&otilde;lmab juurdep&auml;&auml;su kogu kindlustustegevusele, v&auml;lja arvatud elukindlustus, terves &uuml;henduses ning seet&otilde;ttu iga n&otilde;uetekohaselt tegevusloa saanud kindlustusandja v&otilde;imalust kindlustada k&otilde;iki direktiivi 73/239/EM&Uuml; lisas nimetatud riske; sel eesm&auml;rgil tuleb kaotada teatud liikmesriikides m&otilde;nele asutustele kuuluv teatavate riskide kindlustamise monopol; </eesti>
<inglise> (11) Whereas the provisions on transfers of portfolios must be adapted to bring them into line with the single authorization system introduced by this Directive; </inglise>
<eesti> 11) s&auml;tteid portfellide &uuml;leandmiste kohta tuleb kohandada, et viia need vastavusse k&auml;esolevas direktiivis kehtestatud &uuml;htse tegevusloa s&uuml;steemiga; </eesti>
<inglise> (12) Whereas Directive 91/674/EEC has already effected the necessary harmonization of the Member States' rules on the technical provisions which insurers are required to establish to cover their commitments, and that harmonization makes it possible to grant mutual recognition of those provisions; </inglise>
<eesti> 12) direktiiv 91/674/EM&Uuml; on juba j&otilde;ustanud liikmesriikide selliste eeskirjade vajaliku &uuml;htlustamise, mis k&auml;sitlevad kindlustustehnilisi eraldisi, mille loomist n&otilde;utakse kindlustusandjatelt nende kohustuste tagamiseks, ja see &uuml;htlustamine v&otilde;imaldab neid eraldisi vastastikku tunnustada; </eesti>
<inglise> (13) Whereas the rules governing the spread, localization and matching of the assets used to cover technical provisions must be coordinated in order to facilitate the mutual recognition of Member States' rules; whereas that coordination must take account of the measures on the liberalization of capital movements provided for in the Council Directive of 24 June 1988 for the implementation of Article 67 of the Treaty (88/361/EEC) (7) and the progress made by the Community towards economic and monetary union; </inglise>
<eesti> 13) kindlustustehniliste eraldiste tagamiseks kasutatavate varade hajutamist, asukohta ja vastavust reguleerivad eeskirjad tuleb koosk&otilde;lastada, et h&otilde;lbustada liikmesriikide eeskirjade vastastikust tunnustamist; koosk&otilde;lastamisel tuleb arvesse v&otilde;tta kapitaliliikumise liberaliseerimise meetmeid, mis on s&auml;testatud n&otilde;ukogu 24. juuni 1988. aasta direktiiviga asutamislepingu artikli 67 rakendamise kohta (88/361/EM&Uuml;), (7) ning &uuml;henduse edusamme majandus- ja rahaliidu suunas; </eesti>
<inglise> (14) Whereas, however, the home Member State may not require insurance undertakings to invest the assets covering their technical provisions in particular categories of assets, as such a requirement would be incompatible with the measures on the liberalization of capital movements provided for in Directive 88/361/EEC; </inglise>
<eesti> 14) p&auml;ritoluliikmesriik ei v&otilde;i kindlustusseltsidelt n&otilde;uda kindlustustehnilisi eraldiste kattevarade investeerimist teatud kindlatesse varaliikidesse, sest selline n&otilde;ue oleks vastuolus direktiivis 88/361/EM&Uuml; s&auml;testatud kapitaliliikumise liberaliseerimise meetmetega; </eesti>
<inglise> (15) Whereas, pending the adoption of a Directive on investment services harmonizing inter alia the definition of the concept of regulated market, for the purposes of this Directive and without prejudice to such future harmonization that concept must be defined provisionally; whereas that definition will be replaced by that harmonized at Community level which will give the home Member State of the market the responsibilities for these matters which this Directive transitionally gives to the insurance undertaking's home Member State; </inglise>
<eesti> 15) kuni investeerimisteenuseid k&auml;sitleva direktiivi vastuv&otilde;tmiseni, mis muu hulgas &uuml;htlustaks reguleeritud turu m&otilde;iste m&auml;&auml;ratluse, tuleb see m&otilde;iste k&auml;esolevas direktiivis m&auml;&auml;ratleda ajutiselt, ilma et see piiraks k&otilde;nealust edaspidist &uuml;htlustamist; see m&auml;&auml;ratlus asendatakse &uuml;henduse tasandil &uuml;htlustatuga, mis paneb turu asukohaliikmesriigile vastutuse k&uuml;simustes, mille k&auml;esolev direktiiv m&auml;&auml;rab ajutiselt kindlustusseltsi p&auml;ritoluliikmesriigile; </eesti>
<inglise> (16) Whereas the list of items of which the solvency margin required by Directive 73/239/EEC may be made up must be supplemented to take account of new financial instruments and of the facilities granted to other financial institutions for the constitution of their own funds; </inglise>
<eesti> 16) tuleb t&auml;iendada vahendite nimekirja, millest v&otilde;ib koosneda direktiiviga 73/239/EM&Uuml; n&otilde;utav solventsusmarginaal, et v&otilde;tta arvesse uusi rahastamisvahendeid ja muudele rahaasutustele nende omavahendite loomiseks antud v&otilde;imalusi; </eesti>
<inglise> (17) Whereas within the framework of an integrated insurance market policyholders who, by virtue of their status, their size or the nature of the risks to be insured, do not require special protection in the Member State in which a risk is situated should be granted complete freedom to choose the law applicable to their insurance contracts; </inglise>
<eesti> 17) integreeritud kindlustusturu raames tuleks kindlustusv&otilde;tjatele, kes oma seisundi, suuruse v&otilde;i kindlustatava riski laadi t&otilde;ttu ei vaja riski asukohariigis erilist kaitset, anda t&auml;ielik vabadus valida nende kindlustuslepingute suhtes kohaldatav &otilde;igus; </eesti>
<inglise> (18) Whereas the harmonization of insurance contract law is not a prior condition for the achievement of the internal market in insurance; whereas, therefore, the opportunity afforded to the Member States of imposing the application of their law to insurance contracts covering risks situated within their territories is likely to provide adequate safeguards for policyholders who require special protection; </inglise>
<eesti> 18) kindlustuslepingu&otilde;iguse &uuml;htlustamine ei ole kindlustuse siseturu saavutamise eeltingimus; seet&otilde;ttu tagab liikmesriikidele antud v&otilde;imalus kohaldada nende territooriumil asuvaid riske kindlustavate kindlustuslepingute suhtes oma &otilde;igust t&otilde;en&auml;oliselt piisava kaitse kindlustusv&otilde;tjatele, kes vajavad erilist kaitset; </eesti>
<inglise> (19) Whereas within the framework of an internal market it is in the policyholder's interest that he should have access to the widest possible range of insurance products available in the Community so that he can choose that which is best suited to his needs; whereas it is for the Member State in which the risk is situated to ensure that there is nothing to prevent the marketing within its territory of all the insurance products offered for sale in the Community as long as they do not conflict with the legal provisions protecting the general good in force in the Member State in which the risk is situated, and insofar as the general good is not safeguarded by the rules of the home Member State, provided that such provisions must be applied without discrimination to all undertakings operating in that Member State and be objectively necessary and in proportion to the objective pursued; </inglise>
<eesti> 19) siseturu raames on kindlustusv&otilde;tja huvides, et tal oleks juurdep&auml;&auml;s &uuml;henduses k&auml;ttesaadavate kindlustustoodete v&otilde;imalikult laiale valikule, mis v&otilde;imaldab tal nende seast valida tema vajadustele k&otilde;ige paremini vastava; riski asukohaliikmesriik peab tagama, et miski ei takistaks tema territooriumil k&otilde;igi &uuml;henduses m&uuml;&uuml;giks pakutavate kindlustustoodete turustamist, niiv&otilde;rd kui need ei ole vastuolus riski asukohaliikmesriigis kehtivate &uuml;ldist h&uuml;vangut kaitsvate &otilde;igusnormidega ja kui seda &uuml;ldist h&uuml;vangut ei kaitse p&auml;ritoluliikmesriigi eeskirjad, tingimusel et selliseid s&auml;tteid tuleb kohaldada eranditult k&otilde;igi selles liikmesriigis tegutsevate kindlustusseltside suhtes ning et need on objektiivselt vajalikud ja proportsionaalsed taotletava eesm&auml;rgiga; </eesti>
<inglise> (20) Whereas the Member States must be able to ensure that the insurance products and contract documents used, under the right of establishment or the freedom to provide services, to cover risks situated within their territories comply with such specific legal provisions protecting the general good as are applicable; whereas the systems of supervision to be employed must meet the requirements of an integrated market but their employment may not constitute a prior condition for carrying on insurance business; whereas from this standpoint systems for the prior approval of policy conditions do not appear to be justified; whereas it is therefore necessary to provide for other systems better suited to the requirements of an internal market which enable every Member State to guarantee policyholders adequate protection; </inglise>
<eesti> 20) liikmesriigid peavad suutma tagada, et kindlustustooted ja lepingudokumendid, mida asutamis&otilde;iguse ja teenuste osutamise vabaduse alusel kasutatakse nende territooriumil asuvate riskide kindlustamiseks, vastavad kohaldatavatele &uuml;ldist h&uuml;vangut kaitsvatele &otilde;igusnormidele; kasutatavad j&auml;relevalves&uuml;steemid peavad vastama integreeritud turu n&otilde;uetele, kuid nende kasutamine ei v&otilde;i olla kindlustustegevuse eeltingimus; sellelt seisukohalt ei ole lepingutingimuste eelneva heakskiitmise s&uuml;steemid &otilde;igustatud; seet&otilde;ttu on vaja s&auml;testada muud s&uuml;steemid, mis paremini vastaksid siseturu n&otilde;uetele ja v&otilde;imaldaksid liikmesriikidel tagada kindlustusv&otilde;tjatele piisav kaitse; </eesti>
<inglise> (21) Whereas if a policyholder is a natural person, he should be informed by the insurance undertaking of the law which will apply to the contract and of the arrangements for handling policyholders' complaints concerning contracts; </inglise>
<eesti> 21) juhul, kui kindlustusv&otilde;tja on f&uuml;&uuml;siline isik, peaks kindlustusselts talle teatama lepingu suhtes kohaldatava &otilde;iguse ja kindlustusv&otilde;tjate lepinguid k&auml;sitlevate kaebuste k&auml;itlemise korra; </eesti>
<inglise> (22) Whereas in some Member States private or voluntary health insurance serves as a partial or complete alternative to health cover provided for by the social security systems; </inglise>
<eesti> 22) m&otilde;nes liikmesriigis on era- v&otilde;i vabatahtlik tervisekindlustus osaline v&otilde;i t&auml;ielik alternatiiv sotsiaalkindlustuss&uuml;steemidega tagatud tervisekindlustusele; </eesti>
<inglise> (23) Whereas the nature and social consequences of health insurance contracts justify the competent authorities of the Member State in which a risk is situated in requiring systematic notification of the general and special policy conditions in order to verify that such contracts are a partial or complete alternative to the health cover provided by the social security system; whereas such verification must not be a prior condition for the marketing of the products; whereas the particular nature of health insurance, serving as a partial or complete alternative to the health cover provided by the social security system, distinguishes it from other classes of indemnity insurance and life assurance insofar as it is necessary to ensure that policyholders have effective access to private health cover or health cover taken out on a voluntary basis regardless of their age or risk profile; </inglise>
