<inglise> Article 15 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 15 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall require any natural or legal person who proposes to acquire, directly or indirectly, a qualifying holding in an insurance undertaking first to inform the competent authorities of the home Member State, indicating the size of his intended holding. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid kohustavad iga f&uuml;&uuml;silist v&otilde;i juriidilist isikut, kes soovib kas otseselt v&otilde;i kaudselt omandada olulist osalust kindlustusseltsis, teatama sellest k&otilde;igepealt p&auml;ritoluliikmesriigi p&auml;devatele asutustele, n&auml;idates omandatava osaluse suuruse. </eesti>
<inglise> Such a person must likewise inform the competent authorities of the home Member State if he proposes to increase his qualifying holding so that the proportion of the voting rights or of the capital he holds would reach or exceed 20, 33 or 50 % or so that the insurance undertaking would become his subsidiary. </inglise>
<eesti> Samuti peab selline isik teatama p&auml;ritoluliikmesriigi p&auml;devatele asutustele juhul, kui ta taotleb oma olulise osaluse suurendamist sel m&auml;&auml;ral, et tema osa h&auml;&auml;lte arvust v&otilde;i tema omanduses olev kapital on 20%, 33% v&otilde;i 50% v&otilde;i rohkem v&otilde;i ulatub sellise m&auml;&auml;rani, et kindlustusselts muutub tema t&uuml;tarettev&otilde;tjaks. </eesti>
<inglise> The competent authorities of the home Member State shall have up to three months from the date of the notification provided for in the first subparagraph to oppose such a plan if, in view of the need to ensure sound and prudent management of the insurance undertaking in question, they are not satisfied as to the qualification of the person referred to in the first subparagraph. </inglise>
<eesti> P&auml;ritoluliikmesriigi p&auml;devatel asutustel on esimeses l&otilde;igus etten&auml;htud teate esitamise kuup&auml;evast alates kuni kolm kuud aega, et sellisele kavatsusele vastuv&auml;iteid esitada, kui nad, silmas pidades vajadust tagada kindlustusseltsi arukas ja usaldusv&auml;&auml;rne juhtimine, ei ole veendunud esimeses l&otilde;igus m&auml;rgitud isiku kvalifikatsioonis. </eesti>
<inglise> If they do not oppose the plan in question, they may fix a maximum period fort its implementation. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui nad k&otilde;nealusele kavatsusele vastuv&auml;iteid ei esita, v&otilde;ivad nad kindlaks m&auml;&auml;rata selle elluviimise maksimumt&auml;htaja. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall require any natural or legal person who proposes to dispose, directly or indirectly, of a qualifying holding in an insurance undertaking first to inform the competent authorities of the home Member State, indicating the size of his intended holding. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid kohustavad iga f&uuml;&uuml;silist v&otilde;i juriidilist isikut, kes soovib kas otseselt v&otilde;i kaudselt &uuml;le anda olulist osalust kindlustusseltsis, teatama sellest k&otilde;igepealt p&auml;ritoluliikmesriigi p&auml;devatele asutustele, n&auml;idates omandatava osaluse suuruse. </eesti>
