<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> As regard the assets covering technical provisions, the home Member State shall require every insurance undertaking to invest no more than: </inglise>
<eesti> Kindlustustehniliste eraldiste kattevarade puhul n&otilde;uab iga liikmesriik, et &uuml;kski kindlustusselts ei investeeriks rohkem kui: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) 10 % of its total gross technical provisions in any one piece of land or building, or a number of pieces of land or buildings close enough to each other to be considered effectively as one investment; </inglise>
<eesti> a) 10% oma kindlustustehniliste eraldiste kogusummast &uuml;hte konkreetsesse maat&uuml;kki v&otilde;i ehitisse v&otilde;i mitmesse maat&uuml;kki v&otilde;i ehitisse, mis on omavahel nii l&auml;hestikku, et neid loetakse tegelikult &uuml;heks investeeringuks; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) 5 % of its total gross technical provisions in shares and other negotiable securities treated as shares, bonds, debt securities and other money and capital market instruments from the same undertaking, or in loans granted to the same borrower, taken together, the loans being loans other than those granted to a State, regional or local authority or to an international organization of which one or more Member States are members. </inglise>
<eesti> b) 5% oma kindlustustehniliste eraldiste kogusummast sama kindlustusseltsi aktsiatesse ja muudesse vabalt kaubeldavatesse v&auml;&auml;rtpaberitesse, mida k&auml;sitletakse nagu aktsiaid, v&otilde;lakirjadesse, v&otilde;latagatistesse ning muudesse raha- ja kapitalituru vahenditesse, v&otilde;i samale laenusaajale antud laenudesse kokku, kui laene ei anta riigiasutusele, piirkondlikule v&otilde;i kohalikule asutusele v&otilde;i rahvusvahelisele organisatsioonile, mille liikmed on &uuml;ks v&otilde;i mitu liikmesriiki. </eesti>
<inglise> This limit may be raised to 10 % if an undertaking does not invest more than 40 % of its gross technical provisions in the loans or securities of issuing bodies and borrowers in each of which it invests more than 5 % of its assets; </inglise>
<eesti> Seda m&auml;&auml;ra v&otilde;ib t&otilde;sta kuni 10%ni, kui kindlustusselts ei investeeri rohkem kui 40% oma kindlustustehniliste eraldiste summast emiteerivate organite v&otilde;i laenusaajate laenudesse v&otilde;i v&auml;&auml;rtpaberitesse, millest iga&uuml;hesse ta investeerib rohkem kui 5% oma varadest; </eesti>
<inglise> (c) 5 % of its total gross technical provisions in unsecured loans, including 1 % for any single unsecured loan, other than loans granted to credit institutions, assurance undertaking - in so far as Article 8 of Directive 73/239/EEC allows it - and investment undertakings established in a Member State; </inglise>
<eesti> c) 5% oma kindlustustehniliste eraldiste kogusummast tagatiseta laenudesse, sealhulgas 1% iga &uuml;ksiku tagatiseta laenu kohta, kui laenu ei anta krediidiasutustele, kindlustusseltsidele - niiv&otilde;rd kui direktiivi 73/239/EM&Uuml; artikkel 8 seda v&otilde;imaldab - ja m&otilde;nes liikmesriigis asutatud investeerimis&uuml;hingutele; </eesti>
<inglise> (d) 3 % of its total gross technical provisions in the form of cash in hand; </inglise>
<eesti> d) 3% oma kindlustustehniliste eraldiste kogusummast kassas oleva sularaha kujul; </eesti>
<inglise> (e) 10 % of its total gross technical provisions in shares, other securities treated as shares and debt securities, which are not dealt in on a regulated market. </inglise>
<eesti> e) 10% oma kindlustustehniliste eraldiste kogusummast aktsiates, muudes aktsiatena k&auml;sitletavates v&auml;&auml;rtpaberites ja v&otilde;latagatistes, millega ei kaubelda reguleeritud turul. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The absence of a limit in paragraph 1 on investment in any particular category does not imply that assets in that category should be accepted as cover for technical provisions without limit. </inglise>
<eesti> See, et l&otilde;ikes 1 puudub piirang investeeringutele mis tahes konkreetsesse liiki, ei t&auml;henda, et selle liigi varad v&otilde;ib kindlustustehniliste eraldiste kattena piiramatult heaks kiita. </eesti>
<inglise> The home Member State shall lay down more detailed rules fixing the conditions for the use of acceptable assets. </inglise>
<eesti> P&auml;ritoluliikmesriik s&auml;testab &uuml;ksikasjalikumad eeskirjad, mis kinnitavad lubatavate varade kasutamise tingimused. </eesti>
<inglise> In particular it shall ensure, in the determination and the application of those rules, that the following principles are complied with: </inglise>
<eesti> Eriti tagab ta nende eeskirjade kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ramise ja kohaldamisega j&auml;rgmiste p&otilde;him&otilde;tete j&auml;rgimise: </eesti>
<inglise> (i) assets covering technical provisions must be diversified and spread in such a way as to ensure that there is no excessive reliance on any particular category of asset, investment market or investment; </inglise>
<eesti> i) kindlustustehniliste eraldiste kattevarad peavad olema mitmekesistatud ja hajutatud viisil, mis tagab, et puudub &uuml;lem&auml;&auml;rane toetumine teatud liiki varale, investeerimisturule v&otilde;i investeeringule; </eesti>
<inglise> (ii) investment in particular types of asset which show high levels of risk, whether because of the nature of the asset or the quality of the issuer, must be restricted to prudent levels; </inglise>
<eesti> ii) investeerimine konkreetset liiki varasse, millel on k&otilde;rge riskiaste kas siis vara laadi v&otilde;i emiteerija seisundi t&otilde;ttu, tuleb piirata usaldusv&auml;&auml;rse tasemega; </eesti>
<inglise> (iii) limitations on particular categories of asset must take account of the treatment of reinsurance in the calculation of technical provisions; </inglise>
<eesti> iii) konkreetsete varaliikide piirangud peavad arvestama edasikindlustuse k&auml;sitlemist kindlustustehniliste eraldiste arvutamisel; </eesti>
<inglise> (iv) where the assets held include an investment in a subsidiary undertaking which manages all or part of the insurance undertaking's investments on its behalf, the home Member State must, when applying the rules and principles laid down in this Article, take into account the underlying assets held by the subsidiary undertaking; the home Member State may treat the assets of other subsidiaries in the same way; </inglise>
<eesti> iv) kui olemasolevad varad h&otilde;lmavad investeeringut t&uuml;tarettev&otilde;tjasse, kes haldab kindlustusseltsi eest osaliselt v&otilde;i tervikuna tema investeeringuid, peab p&auml;ritoluliikmesriik k&auml;esolevas artiklis s&auml;testatud eeskirjade ja p&otilde;him&otilde;tete rakendamisel arvestama t&uuml;tarettev&otilde;tja vastavaid varasid; p&auml;ritoluliikmesriik v&otilde;ib samal viisil k&auml;sitleda teiste t&uuml;tarettev&otilde;tjate varasid; </eesti>
<inglise> (v) the percentage of assets covering technical provisions which are the subject of non-liquid investments must be kept to a prudent level; </inglise>
<eesti> v) kindlustustehnilisi eraldisi katvate mittelikviidsetest investeeringutest s&otilde;ltuvate varade protsent tuleb hoida usaldusv&auml;&auml;rsel tasemel; </eesti>
<inglise> (vi) where the assets held include loans to or debt securities issued by certain credit institutions, the home Member State may, when applying the rules and principles laid down in this Article, take into account the underlying assets held by such credit institutions. </inglise>
<eesti> vi) kui varad h&otilde;lmavad laene teatavatele krediidiasutustele v&otilde;i nende antud v&otilde;latagatisi, v&otilde;ib p&auml;ritoluliikmesriik k&auml;esolevas artiklis s&auml;testatud eeskirjade ja p&otilde;him&otilde;tete kohaldamisel arvestada selliste krediidiasutuste vastavaid varasid. </eesti>
<inglise> This treatment may be applied only where the credit institution has its head office in a Member State, is entirely owned by that Member State and/or that State's local authorities and its business, according to its memorandum and articles of association, consists of extending, through its intermediary, loans to or guaranteed by the State or local authorities or loans to bodies closely linked to the State or to local authorities. </inglise>
<eesti> Seda re&zcaron;iimi v&otilde;ib kohaldada ainult juhul, kui krediidiasutuse peakontor asub liikmesriigis, kuulub t&auml;ielikult liikmesriigile ja/v&otilde;i selle riigi kohalikele asutustele ning tema tegevus seisneb vastavalt asutamislepingule ja p&otilde;hikirjale laenude vahendamises riigile v&otilde;i kohalikele asutustele v&otilde;i nende tagatisega laenude vahendamises v&otilde;i laenude vahendamises riigi v&otilde;i kohalike asutustega tihedalt seotud organitele. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> In the context of the detailed rules laying down the conditions for the use of acceptable assets, the Member State shall give more limitative treatment to: </inglise>
<eesti> Seoses vastuv&otilde;etavate varade kasutamise tingimusi s&auml;testavate &uuml;ksikasjaliste eeskirjadega k&auml;sitleb liikmesriik piiravamalt: </eesti>
<inglise> - any loan unaccompanied by a bank guarantee, a guarantee issued by an insurance undertaking, a mortgage or any other form of security, as compared with loans accompanied by such collateral, </inglise>
<eesti> - k&otilde;iki laene, millega ei kaasne pangatagatist, kindlustusseltsi antud tagatist, h&uuml;poteeki v&otilde;i muud tagatisevormi, v&otilde;rrelduna laenudega, millele on selline tagatis, </eesti>
<inglise> - Ucits not coordinated within the meaning of Directive 85/611/EEC(13) and other investment funds, as compared with Ucits coordinated within the meaning of that Directive, </inglise>
