<inglise> Branches which have started business, in accordance with the provisions in force in their Member State of establishment, before the entry into force of the provisions adopted in implementation of this Directive shall be presumed to have been subject to the procedure laid down in Article 10 (1) to (5) of Directive 73/239/EEC. </inglise>
<eesti> Filiaalid, kes on alustanud tegevust vastavalt nende asukohaliikmesriikides kehtivatele s&auml;tetele enne k&auml;esoleva direktiivi rakendamiseks vastu v&otilde;etud s&auml;tete j&otilde;ustumist, loetakse direktiivi 73/239/EM&Uuml; artikli 10 l&otilde;igetes 1-5 s&auml;testatud korra kohasteks. </eesti>
<inglise> They shall be governed, from the date of that entry into force, by Articles 15, 19, 20 and 22 of Directive 73/239/EEC and by Article 40 of this Directive. </inglise>
<eesti> Neid reguleerivad alates k&otilde;nealusest j&otilde;ustumiskuup&auml;evast direktiivi 73/239/EM&Uuml; artiklid 15, 19, 20 ja 22 ning k&auml;esoleva direktiivi artikkel 40. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Articles 34 and 35 shall not affect rights acquired by insurance undertakings carrying on business under the freedom to provide services before the entry into force of the provisions adopted in implementation of this Directive. </inglise>
<eesti> Artiklid 34 ja 35 ei m&otilde;juta &otilde;igusi, mille on saanud enne k&auml;esoleva direktiivi rakendamiseks vastuv&otilde;etud s&auml;tete j&otilde;ustumist teenuste osutamise vabaduse alusel tegutsevad kindlustusseltsid. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 53 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 53 </eesti>
<inglise> The following Article shall be inserted in Directive 73/239/EEC: </inglise>
<eesti> Direktiivile 73/239/EM&Uuml; lisatakse j&auml;rgmine artikkel: </eesti>
<inglise> 'Article 28a </inglise>
<eesti> "Artikkel 28a </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Under the conditions laid down by national law, each Member State shall authorize agencies and branches set up within its territory and covered by this Title to transfer all or part of their portfolios of contracts to an accepting office established in the same Member State if the competent authorities of that Member State or, if appropriate, of the Member State referred to in Article 26 certify that after taking the transfer into account the accepting office possesses the necessary solvency margin. </inglise>
<eesti> Iga liikmesriik lubab siseriiklikus &otilde;iguses etten&auml;htud tingimustel tema territooriumil tegutsevatel ja k&auml;esoleva jaotisega h&otilde;lmatud esindustel ja filiaalidel oma lepinguportfelli osaliselt v&otilde;i tervikuna &uuml;le anda samas liikmesriigis asutatud vastuv&otilde;tvale kindlustusseltsile, kui selle liikmesriigi v&otilde;i vajaduse korral artiklis 26 nimetatud liikmesriigi p&auml;devad asutused t&otilde;endavad, et p&auml;rast &uuml;leandmise arvestamist on vastuv&otilde;tval kindlustusseltsil vajalik solventsusmarginaal. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Under the conditions laid down by national law, each Member State shall authorize agencies and branches set up within its territory and covered by this Title to transfer all or part of their portfolios of contracts to an insurance undertaking with a head office in another Member State if the competent authorities of that Member State certify that after taking the transfer into account the accepting office possesses the necessary solvency margin. </inglise>
<eesti> Iga liikmesriik lubab siseriiklikus &otilde;iguses etten&auml;htud tingimustel tema territooriumil tegutsevatel ja k&auml;esoleva jaotisega h&otilde;lmatud esindustel ja filiaalidel oma lepinguportfelli osaliselt v&otilde;i tervikuna &uuml;le anda kindlustusseltsile, kelle peakontor asub teises liikmesriigis, kui selle liikmesriigi p&auml;devad asutused t&otilde;endavad, et p&auml;rast &uuml;leandmise arvestamist on vastuv&otilde;tval kindlustusseltsil vajalik solventsusmarginaal. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> If under the conditions laid down by national law a Member State authorizes agencies and branches set up within its territory and covered by this Title to transfer all or part of their portfolios of contracts to an agency or branch covered by this Title and set up within the territory of another Member State it shall ensure that the competent authorities of the Member State of the accepting office or, if appropriate, of the Member State referred to in Article 26 certify that after taking the transfer into account the accepting office possesses the necessary solvency margin, that the law of the Member State of the accepting office permits such a transfer and that that State has agreed to the transfer. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui liikmesriik siseriiklikes &otilde;igusaktides etten&auml;htud tingimustel lubab tema territooriumil tegutsevatel ja k&auml;esoleva jaotisega h&otilde;lmatud esindustel ja filiaalidel oma lepinguportfelli osaliselt v&otilde;i tervikuna &uuml;le anda k&auml;esoleva jaotisega h&otilde;lmatud ja teises liikmesriigis asutatud esindusele v&otilde;i filiaalile, tagab ta, et vastuv&otilde;tva kindlustusseltsi liikmesriigi v&otilde;i vajaduse korral artiklis 26 nimetatud liikmesriigi p&auml;devad asutused t&otilde;endavad, et p&auml;rast &uuml;leandmise arvestamist on vastuv&otilde;tval kindlustusseltsil vajalik solventsusmarginaal, et vastuv&otilde;tva kindlustusseltsi liikmesriigi &otilde;igus lubab sellist &uuml;leandmist ja et see riik on &uuml;leandmisega n&otilde;ustunud. </eesti>
<inglise> 4. </inglise>
<eesti> 4. </eesti>
<inglise> In the circumstances referred to in paragraphs 1, 2 and 3 the Member State in which the transferring agency or branch is situated shall authorize the transfer after obtaining the agreement of the competent authorities of the Member State in which the risks are situated, where different from the Member State in which the transferring agency or branch is situated. </inglise>
<eesti> L&otilde;igetes 1, 2 ja 3 nimetatud tingimustel lubab &uuml;leandva esinduse v&otilde;i filiaali asukohaliikmesriik &uuml;leandmise, kui ta on saanud riskide asukohaliikmesriigi p&auml;devate asutuste n&otilde;usoleku, juhul kui see pole &uuml;leandva esinduse v&otilde;i filiaali asukohaliikmesriik. </eesti>
<inglise> 5. </inglise>
<eesti> 5. </eesti>
<inglise> The competent authorities of the Member States consulted shall give their opinion or consent to the competent authorities of the home Member State of the transferring insurance undertaking within three months of receiving a request; the absence of any response from the authorities consulted within that period shall be considered equivalent to a favourable opinion or tacit consent. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriikide konsulteeritavad p&auml;devad asutused esitavad oma arvamuse v&otilde;i annavad n&otilde;usoleku &uuml;leandva kindlustusseltsi p&auml;ritoluliikmesriigi p&auml;devatele asutustele kolme kuu jooksul p&auml;rast taotluse saamist; igasuguse konsulteeritavate asutuste vastuse puudumine selle ajavahemiku jooksul loetakse v&otilde;rdseks soodsa arvamuse v&otilde;i vaikiva n&otilde;usolekuga. </eesti>
<inglise> 6. </inglise>
<eesti> 6. </eesti>
<inglise> A transfer authorized in accordance with this Article shall be published as laid down by national law in the Member State in which the risk is situated. </inglise>
<eesti> Vastavalt k&auml;esolevale artiklile lubatud &uuml;leandmine avaldatakse siseriiklikes &otilde;igusaktides s&auml;testatud tingimustel riski asukohaliikmesriigis. </eesti>
<inglise> Such transfers shall automatically be valid against policyholders, insured persons and any other persons having rights or obligations arising out of the contracts transferred. </inglise>
<eesti> Selline &uuml;leandmine j&otilde;ustub automaatselt kindlustusv&otilde;tjate, kindlustatud isikute ja muude &uuml;leantud lepingutest tulenevate &otilde;iguste v&otilde;i kohustustega isikute suhtes. </eesti>
<inglise> This provision shall not affect the Member States' right to give policyholders the option of cancelling contracts within a fixed period after a transfer. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev s&auml;te ei m&otilde;juta liikmesriikide &otilde;igust anda kindlustusv&otilde;tjatele v&otilde;imalus kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ratud ajavahemiku jooksul p&auml;rast &uuml;leandmist lepingud l&otilde;petada." </eesti>
<inglise> Article 54 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 54 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Notwithstanding any provision to the contrary, a Member State in which contracts covering the risks in class 2 of point A of the Annex to Directive 73/239/EEC may serve as a partial or complete alternative to health cover provided by the statutory social security system may requrie that those contracts comply with the specific legal provisions adopted by that Member State to porotect the general good in that class of insurance, and that the general and special conditions of that insurance be communicated to the competent authorities of that Member State before use. </inglise>
<eesti> Vaatamata k&otilde;igile vastupidistele s&auml;tetele v&otilde;ib liikmesriik, kus riikliku sotsiaalkindlustuss&uuml;steemi antud tervisekindlustuse asemel v&otilde;ib osaliselt v&otilde;i t&auml;ielikult kasutada direktiivi 73/239/EM&Uuml; lisa punkti A liigi 2 riske kindlustavaid lepinguid, n&otilde;uda, et need lepingud j&auml;rgiksid selle liikmesriigi kehtestatud konkreetseid &otilde;igusnorme selles kindlustusliigis &uuml;ldise h&uuml;vangu kaitseks, ja et selle kindlustuse &uuml;ld- ja eritingimused edastataks enne kasutamist liikmesriigi p&auml;devatele asutustele. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States may require that the health insurance system referred to in paragraph 1 be operated on a technical basis similar to that of life assurance where: </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid v&otilde;ivad n&otilde;uda, et l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud tervisekindlustuss&uuml;steemi hallataks samasugusel tehnilisel alusel kui elukindlustust, kui: </eesti>
<inglise> - the premiums paid are calculated on the basis of sickness tables and other statistical data relevant to the Member State in which the risk is situated in accordance with the mathematical methods used in insurance, </inglise>
<eesti> - tasutavad kindlustusmaksed arvutatakse vastavalt riski asukohaliikmesriigis kasutatavatele haigestumustabelitele ja muudele statistilistele andmetele koosk&otilde;las kindlustuses kasutatavate matemaatiliste meetoditega, </eesti>
<inglise> - a reserve is set up for increasing age, </inglise>
<eesti> - ea pikenemise tarvis luuakse varu, </eesti>
<inglise> - the insurer may cancel the contract only within a fixed period determined by the Member State in which the risk is situated, </inglise>
<eesti> - kindlustaja v&otilde;ib lepingu l&otilde;petada ainult riski asukohaliikmesriigi m&auml;&auml;ratud kindla t&auml;htaja jooksul, </eesti>
<inglise> - the contract provides that premiums may be increased or payments reduced, even for current contracts, </inglise>
<eesti> - leping n&auml;eb ette, et kindlustusmakseid v&otilde;ib isegi kehtivate lepingute puhul suurendada v&otilde;i v&auml;ljamakseid v&auml;hendada, </eesti>
<inglise> - the contract provides that the policyholder may change his existing contract into a new contract complying with paragraph 1, offered by the same insurance undertaking or the same branch and taking account of his acquired rights. </inglise>
<eesti> - leping s&auml;testab, et kindlustusv&otilde;tja v&otilde;ib vahetada oma senise lepingu uue, l&otilde;ikele 1 vastava lepingu vastu, mida pakub sama kindlustusselts v&otilde;i sama filiaal ja mis v&otilde;tab arvesse tema omandatud &otilde;igusi. </eesti>
<inglise> In particular, account must be taken of the reserve for increasing age and a new medical examination may be required only for increased cover. </inglise>
<eesti> Eriti tuleb arvesse v&otilde;tta pikeneva ea varu ja uut meditsiinilist l&auml;bivaatust v&otilde;ib n&otilde;uda ainult kindlustuskatte suurendamise korral. </eesti>
<inglise> In that event, the competent authorities of the Member State concerned shall publish the sickness tables and other relevant statistical data referred to in the first subparagraph and transmit them to the competent authorities of the home Member State. </inglise>
<eesti> Sel juhul avaldavad asjaomase liikmesriigi p&auml;devad asutused esimeses taandes nimetatud haigestumustabelid ja muud asjakohased statistilised andmed ning edastavad need p&auml;ritoluliikmesriigi p&auml;devatele asutustele. </eesti>
<inglise> The premiums must be sufficient, on rasonable actuarial assumptions, for undertakings to be able to meet all their commitments having regard to all aspects of their financial situation. </inglise>
<eesti> Kindlustusmaksed peavad m&otilde;istliku aktuaarhinnangu kohaselt olema piisavad, et kindlustusseltsid saaksid t&auml;ita k&otilde;iki oma kohustusi, pidades silmas k&otilde;iki oma finantsseisundi aspekte. </eesti>
<inglise> The home Member State shall require that the technical basis for the calculation of premiums be communicated to its competent authorities before the product is circulated. </inglise>
<eesti> P&auml;ritoluliikmesriik n&otilde;uab, et kindlustusmaksete arvutamise tehniline alus edastataks enne toote ringlusse laskmist tema p&auml;devatele asutustele. </eesti>
<inglise> This paragraph shall also apply where existing contracts are modified. </inglise>
<eesti> Samuti kohaldatakse k&auml;esolevat l&otilde;iget seniste lepingute muutmise korral. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 55 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 55 </eesti>
<inglise> Member States may require that any insurance undertaking offering, at its own risk, compulsory insurance against accidents at work within their territories comply with the specific provisions of their national law concerning such insurance, except for the provisions concerning financial supervision, which shall be the exclusive responsibility of the home Member State. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid v&otilde;ivad n&otilde;uda, et iga kindlustusselts, kes nende territooriumil omal vastutusel pakub kohustuslikku t&ouml;&ouml;&otilde;nnetuskindlustust, j&auml;rgiks siseriikliku &otilde;iguse sellist kindlustust k&auml;sitlevaid s&auml;tteid, v&auml;lja arvatud finantsj&auml;relevalvet k&auml;sitlevad s&auml;tted, mis on ainult p&auml;ritoluliikmesriigi kohustus. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 56 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 56 </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall ensure that decisions taken in respect of an isurance undertaking under laws, regulations and administrative provisions adopted in accordance with this Directive may be subject to the right to apply to the courts. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid tagavad, et kindlustusseltse k&auml;sitlevate otsuste puhul, mis on tehtud k&auml;esoleva direktiiviga koosk&otilde;las kehtestatud &otilde;igusnormide alusel, on &otilde;igus p&ouml;&ouml;rduda kohtusse. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 57 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 57 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The Member States shall adopt the laws, regulations and administrative provisions necessary for their compliance with this Directive not later than 31 December 1993 and bring them into force no later than 1 July 1994. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid v&otilde;tavad k&auml;esoleva direktiivi j&auml;rgimiseks vajalikud &otilde;igusnormid vastu hiljemalt 31. detsembril 1993 ja j&otilde;ustavad need hiljemalt 1. juulil 1994. </eesti>
<inglise> They shall forthwith inform the Commission thereof. </inglise>
<eesti> Nad teatavad sellest viivitamata komisjonile. </eesti>
<inglise> When they adopt such measures the Member States shall include references to this Directive or shall make such references when they effect official publication. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui liikmesriigid need meetmed vastu v&otilde;tavad, viidatakse nendes k&auml;esolevale direktiivile v&otilde;i lisatakse sellised viited neile ametliku avaldamise korral. </eesti>
<inglise> The manner in which such references are to be made shall be laid down by the Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> Sellise viitamise viisi n&auml;evad ette liikmesriigid. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The Member States shall communicate to the Commission the texts of the main provisions of national law which they adopt in the field covered by this Directive. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid edastavad komisjonile k&auml;esoleva direktiiviga reguleeritavas valdkonnas nende poolt vastuv&otilde;etud siseriiklike p&otilde;hiliste &otilde;igusnormide teksti. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 58 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 58 </eesti>
<inglise> This Directive is addressed to the Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev direktiiv on adresseeritud liikmesriikidele. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Luxembourg, 18 June 1992. </inglise>
